com.jalapeno.annotations
Annotation Type Extends

@Target(value=TYPE)
@Retention(value=RUNTIME)
public @interface Extends

Extend annotation replaces the default superclass of generated Cache Class. The default class is determined by the following rule: - If the given class extends another Java class (other than java.lang.Object) and its superclass was not excluded from projection to Cache (i.e. was not added to the list of exclusions) then Cache projection of the superclass becomes a superclass in Cache - If: 1) The given class extends java.lang.Object or a java class that has been excluded from projections and 2) Its type is persistent then its superclass is %Library.Persistent - If: 1) The given class extends java.lang.Object or a java class that has been excluded from projections and 2) It is defined as embeddable (its type is serial) then its superclass is %Library.SerialObject
